						               													<description>Halloween Hustle is played with a standard deck of cards and a supply of candy (or other small items).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of each hand each player receives four cards and a supply of candy is placed in the center of the table: one less than the number of players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dealer draws a card from the deck and then passes any of their cards to the player on their left, who then passes any card to the next player, and so on; the player to the right of the dealer ends up discarding a card. In the meantime the dealer draws and passes another card, so players end up all passing cards at the same time. Discards are shuffled when the deck runs out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player has four cards of the same rank they take a piece of candy. All other players may then also take a piece. Starting on the second round the player left without a piece is eliminated from the game. After a player is eliminated, of one player has more candy than anyone else they win. Otherwise another hand is played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player may pretend to be about to take a piece of candy to fake out other players. If another player takes a piece in this case, they must give it back along with a piece they already have.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variant rules are provided for younger children.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(The game says up to 13 players can play, but there's no way to get the game started in that case.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
